    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1221023007" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1221023007" />
    <a title="David Rubenstein" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/155663-david-rubenstein"><img alt="David Rubenstein" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581956036p2/155663.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1221023007?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="David Rubenstein" class="user" itemprop="url" name="David Rubenstein" href="/user/show/155663-david-rubenstein">David Rubenstein</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to David by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/5448792-b-schrodinger">B Schrodinger</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/155663-david-rubenstein?shelf=humor">humor</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/155663-david-rubenstein?shelf=science">science</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1221023007" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3591956491602048355">Randall Munroe is a dangerous guy. Seriously dangerous. He is the author of the online comic strip <a href='http://xkcd.com' rel='nofollow noopener'>xkcd</a>. It&apos;s about math, science, hacking, logic, and a host of wonderfully nerdy subjects. But in this book, Munroe answers a stack of absurd hypothetical questions. Some of the questions are really crazy, like &quot;<i>What would happen if everyone on Earth stood as close to each other as they could and jumped, everyone landing on the ground at the same instant?</i>&quot; Munroe explains that the &quot;thud&quot; as everyone</span>
  <span id="freeText3591956491602048355" style="display:none">Randall Munroe is a dangerous guy. Seriously dangerous. He is the author of the online comic strip <a href="http://xkcd.com" rel="nofollow noopener">xkcd</a>. It's about math, science, hacking, logic, and a host of wonderfully nerdy subjects. But in this book, Munroe answers a stack of absurd hypothetical questions. Some of the questions are really crazy, like "<i>What would happen if everyone on Earth stood as close to each other as they could and jumped, everyone landing on the ground at the same instant?</i>" Munroe explains that the "thud" as everyone came down at the same time wouldn't amount to much. But, the aftermath would be catastrophic.<br><br>But what's really crazy, is how Munroe takes bland questions and hypes them into incredible zingers. For example, "<i>If every person on Earth aimed a laser pointer at the Moon at the same time, would it change color?</i>" The answer, of course, is "no". But Munroe never stops with an answer like that. He ups the ante, increasing the power of the laser pointers, to the point where he becomes <i>really</i> dangerous!<br><br>What is truly wonderful about this book, is that the answers are explained with scientific reasoning. Occasionally the answers are speculative, but this is clearly spelled out. Munroe usually applies scientific principles to answer the questions correctly, regardless of the level of absurdity. And, the questions and answers are all illustrated with his stick-figure cartoons, adding appreciably to the humor.<img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1425746819i/13927255.png" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
  <a data-text-id="3591956491602048355" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review1221023007">
